title: Palestinian Aid Organiser Describes Australia-Funded Gaza Health Clinic | 10 News+
description: Mohammad Asideh works for Rozana Project, an organisation supported by both Australian government grants and donations from everyday Aussies. He has led a Rozana mission establishing a health clinic in the ruins of the Gaza Strip. During an interview in his brief trip back to Australia, Asideh described the conditions in Gaza. His team recruited local doctors and nurses for the tent clinic, which now provides services to around 2,500 people each month. title: Wieambilla Inquest Finds Killers Had “Delusion Disorder” But Were Not Terrorists | 10 News
description: Two police officers and a neighbour, murdered in Wieambilla in what was, at the time, described as Australia's first Christian terror attack.  But today Queensland's chief coroner says it doesn't meet the definition of 'terror'.  Instead calling the killers “delusional conspiracists” who would rather die  than be captured. title: 11 Injured After Grizzly Bear Attacks School Group In Canada | 10 News
description: A grizzly bear is on the loose after attacking a school group in Canada’s British Columbia, leaving 11 people injured.  It’s understood the students and teachers stopped along a walking trail in the town of Bella Coola when a grizzly bear emerged from the forest and attacked, before several teachers used spray and a banger to try drive the bear away.  Three children and one adult were seriously injured, while another seven people required medical attention at the scene.  Residents have been warned to remain indoors while armed officers try to track down the animal. title: Trump Praises New York Mayor-Elect Zohran Mamdani After White House Meeting | 10 News
description: US President Donald Trump has praised New York City Mayor-elect Zohran Mamdani after cordial talks at the White House.  Trump previously threatened to cut funding to New York if Mamdani was elected, but now says they have pledged to work together to lower living costs in America's biggest city and stated Mamdani will “do a very good job” as the incoming mayor.  The pair spoke about housing, food prices and energy costs, adding that efforts to bring prices down nationally would "be good for New York." title: Republican Marjorie Taylor Greene To Resign From US Congress After Fallout With Trump | 10 News
description: Republican Marjorie Taylor Greene has announced her resignation from US Congress, following a recent falling out with Trump.  Greene made the announcement via a 10-minute video posted to the social media platform X, stating she will be resigning from office effective January 5, 2026.  “No matter which way the political pendulum swings, Republican or Democrat, nothing ever gets better for the common American man or woman,” Greene said.  The US President branded Greene a "traitor" and "wacky" after the congresswoman criticised him for his stance on files related to Jeffrey Epstein. title: A Man & Teenager Charged After Allegedly Shooting Up Sydney Home | 10 News

title: Anthony Albanese Hopeful Free Trade Agreement With Europe Locked In By 2026 | 10 News
description: Australia is on the cusp of a locking in a major trade deal with Europe on the eve of the G20 Summit in South Africa.  After more than seven years of negotiations, Prime Minister Anthony Albanese is hopeful an agreement can be reached soon following talks with his EU counterparts.

title: Pilot Dead After Indian Fighter Jet Crashes At Dubai Air Show | 10 News
